commitResults.messageTitle: Bugfix for case when save file does not exist
commitResults.messageBody:
Also, edited some comments and made minor edits to the
build.gradle file.

Code does not make use of assertions.

Adding assertions will help to avoid situations where a bug has
occurred but the code continues to run, potentially causing damage
to saved data.

Let's add assertions to various classes.

This will prevent damaging bugs from occurring.

We shall also make some edits to JavaDocs and use Platform.exit() to
exit from the GUI when the users wants to.

There is repeated code in the String related methods for the Task
subclasses.

This is unnecessary and harder to understand. It can be simplified.

Let's
* refactor the code such that it is simpler
* remove similar code

This will make the code easier to view and simpler to understand.

Other changes that can be made include:
* Remove unused method in the Ui class
* Add a constant for the minimum length of a input array
  in the Parser class

commitResults.messageTitle: Add help command to the chatbot
commitResults.messageBody:
Users do not have access to the commands usable by the chatbot.

This will cause users to be unable to use the full potential of the
chatbot.

Let's add a help command to the chatbot so that users have access to the
list of commands the chatbot accepts.

This will allow users to use the chatbot more easily.
